@remark ----------------------------------------------------------------------

@node MAIN "Browser"
                                   @{b}Browser@{ub}
                   Copyright © 1998 by Olaf `Olsen' Barthel
                             All Rights Reserved

Browser is a combination of a file system explorer and a text viewer. It
allows you to browse the contents of your hard disk, CD-ROMs and floppy disks
without having to type the names of the files you want to view or to enter the
names of the volumes and drawers you wish to examine. This functionality is
coupled with powerful text and file find features, i.e. you can use Browser to
locate every occurance of a string in a file and you can use the program to
locate every file on your hard disk that matches a pattern.

This documentation is designed to be read with Browser running in the
background; just hit the @{b}[Help]@{ub} key and Browser will display the help text
belonging to the window or the control the mouse pointer is currently over.
But you can also use the list of help topics as listed below:

@{" List of startup options...                " link MAIN.OPTIONS}
@{" List of keyboard shortcuts...             " link KEYBOARD}
@{" List of mouse commands...                 " link MOUSE}
@{" List of menu items...                     " link MENU.MAIN}
@{" How to search for text in a file...       " link FIND.TEXT.MAIN}
@{" How to search for a file...               " link FIND.FILE.MAIN}
@{" AppWindow Workbench usage...              " link MAIN.APPWINDOW}
@{" Further information about this program... " link MAIN.ABOUT}
@{" Release history                           " link MAIN.HISTORY}
@endnode

@remark ----------------------------------------------------------------------

@node MAIN.HISTORY "Release history"
Browser 1.48 (30.5.98)

	- The "Copy" menu item now copies the name of the
	  currently highlighted file name in the list
	  instead of the name currently displayed in the
	  text area.

	- Added a new keyboard shortcut to move up to the parent
	  directory ("/").

	- When browsing through cached directory lists, the list
	  top line number is now preserved. Thus, if you enter a
	  directory down at the bottom of a long directory list
	  going back up a level will put you back at the end of
	  the list instead of at the top.

	- Added a new menu item to release the memory allocated
	  for cached directories that are not currently being
	  displayed.

	- The directory list can now be scrolled freely using
	  the numeric keypad. To scroll around in the text
	  display, use the "regular" cursor keys instead.

	- Added a new menu item to stop reading from a file.

	- When reading a file, Browser now examines the first
	  128 bytes to see whether the file in question is a
	  plain text or binary file. If there are less than 75%
	  plain text characters in these first 128 bytes, then
	  the file contents will be displayed in hexadecimal
	  format [Martin Bernd].

Browser 1.47 (26.4.98)

	- Holding down any [Shift] key and clicking on a file will now
	  properly open the file in the next view.

Browser 1.46 (26.4.98)

	- The numeric keypad can now be used to browse the text.

	- The [Space] bar now works much like it did in the "More" utility,
	  i.e. it would scroll the text displayed down a page.

	- Fixed a bug in the directory scanning code which could cause
	  patches like NewIcons to crash [Jim Cooper].

Browser 1.45 (23.4.98)

	- Lines no longer stay highlighted from a previous text search operation
	  when a new file is opened.

Browser 1.44 (23.4.98)

	- Better error handling in the initialization code.

	- Clearer semantics in the item allocation/deallocation code.

Browser 1.43 (23.4.98)

	- Changed the rules that define whether a directory entry is a drawer
	  or a file.

Browser 1.42 (23.4.98)

	- Multiple file names/drawers can now be opened when launching
	  the program.

Browser 1.41 (23.4.98)

	- Modified the algorithm used for finding the help text file.

Browser 1.40 (13.4.98)

	- Fixed two Wipeout hits in the directory context duplication code

Browser 1.39 (10.4.98)

	- Updated the search/scan progress display.

Browser 1.38 (9.4.98)

	- Added search text/pattern history

Browser 1.37 (9.4.98)

	- Added new mouse command [Shift]-[Middle mouse button]

	- Added directory caching

Browser 1.36 (8.4.98)

	- First public release
@endnode

@remark ----------------------------------------------------------------------

@node MAIN.APPWINDOW "AppWindow Workbench usage"
Every Browser window is an AppWindow, i.e. you can drag an icon on the window
and have Browser read the corresponding directory and show the corresponding
file.
@endnode

@remark ----------------------------------------------------------------------

@node KEYBOARD "Keyboard shortcuts"
@{b}                 [F 1]@{ub} @{"Stack windows" link MENU.STACKWINDOWS}
@{b}                 [F 2]@{ub} @{"Tile windows" link MENU.TILEWINDOWS}
@{b}                 [F 3]@{ub} @{"Cascade windows" link MENU.CASCADEWINDOWS}

@{b}                [Help]@{ub} Display help text

@{b}                 [Esc]@{ub} @{"Close active Browser window" link MENU.CLOSE}
@{b}              [Ctrl]-C@{ub} @{"Close active Browser window" link MENU.CLOSE}

@{b}                 [Tab]@{ub} Select next file or drawer name
@{b}         [Shift]-[Tab]@{ub} Select previous file or drawer name

@{b}           [Backspace]@{ub} @{"Go to parent directory" link MENU.PARENT}
@{b}                     /@{ub} @{"Go to parent directory" link MENU.PARENT}

@{b}              [Return]@{ub} @{"Open selected drawer or display selected file" link MENU.OPEN}

@{b}     [Alt]-[Cursor up]@{ub} Move to top of text file
@{b}   [Shift]-[Cursor up]@{ub} Move one page up in the text file
@{b}           [Cursor up]@{ub} Move one line up in the text file

@{b}   [Alt]-[Cursor left]@{ub} Move to left edge of text file
@{b} [Shift]-[Cursor left]@{ub} Move one page left in the text file
@{b}         [Cursor left]@{ub} Move one column left in the text file

@{b}   [Alt]-[Cursor down]@{ub} Move to beginning of text file
@{b} [Shift]-[Cursor down]@{ub} Move one page down in the text file
@{b}         [Cursor down]@{ub} Move one line down in the text file

@{b}  [Alt]-[Cursor right]@{ub} Move to right edge of text file
@{b}[Shift]-[Cursor right]@{ub} Move one page right in the text file
@{b}        [Cursor right]@{ub} Move one column right in the text file

@{b}  [Ctrl]-[Cursor up]@{ub}   Increase size of text display
@{b}  [Ctrl]-[Cursor down]@{ub} Decrease size of text display

@{b}               [Space]@{ub} Move one page down in the text file

The numeric keypad can be used to move around in the directory list.
@endnode

@remark ----------------------------------------------------------------------

@node MOUSE "Mouse commands"
@{b}          [Left mouse button]@{ub} Display file contents or enter drawer

@{b}  [Shift]-[Left mouse button]@{ub} @{"Display drawer contents in next Browser window" link MENU.OPENNEXT}

@{b}        [Middle mouse button]@{ub} Display list of volumes and assignments

@{b}[Shift]-[Middle mouse button]@{ub} @{"Move up to parent directory" link MENU.PARENT}
@endnode

@remark ----------------------------------------------------------------------

@node MAIN.OPTIONS "Startup options"
Browser can be started both from shell and from Workbench. You can control the
look, position size, layout and appearance of the Browser window through
command line parameters and icon tool types. In both cases the option syntax
will be same.

    @{b}DRAWER@{ub}=<Name>
    @{b}FILE@{ub}=<Name>

        This selects the name of the drawer or file to be displayed when the
        Browser window is opened. The default is an empty window. When launched
        from the Workbench, Browser will load every selected drawer and file;
        when launched from Shell, every given file/drawer will be loaded, you
        may even specify the files/drawers to load via wildcard patterns.

    @{b}PUBSCREEN@{ub}=<Name>

        This selects the name of the public screen the Browser window is to
        open on. The default is the default public screen which in most
        cases is the Workbench screen. If the named public screen cannot be
        found, then the window will open on the default public screen.

    @{b}LEFT@{ub}=<Window left edge>

        This sets the left edge of the Browser window to open. Default is
        the leftmost position that allows the Browser window to be seen.

    @{b}TOP@{ub}=<Window top edge>

        This sets the top edge of the Browser window to open. Default is
        the topmost position that allows the Browser window to be seen.

    @{b}WIDTH@{ub}=<Window width>

        This selects the width of the Browser window to open. This value
        must be given in pixels. Default is about 400 pixels.

    @{b}HEIGHT@{ub}=<Window height>

        This selects the height of the Browser window to open. This value
        must be given in pixels. Default is about 200 pixels.

    @{b}DIRLINES@{ub}=<Number of lines in directory display>

        This selects the number of lines to be displayed in the directory
        list at the top of the Browser window. This value affects the
        height of the window and overrides the @{b}HEIGHT@{ub} parameter.

    @{b}TEXTCOLUMNS@{ub}=<Number of columns in text display>

        This selects the number of columns to be displayed in the text
        display at the bottom of the Browser window. This value affects the
        width of the window and overrides the @{b}WIDTH@{ub} parameter.

    @{b}TEXTLINES@{ub}=<Number of lines in text display>

        This selects the number of lines to be displayed in the text
        display at the bottom of the Browser window. This value affects the
        height of the window and overrides the @{b}HEIGHT@{ub} parameter.
@endnode

@node MAIN.ABOUT "Information about Browser"
@{b}Purpose@{ub}
This program was written since I needed a simple and easy way to compare the
compiler and linker options in makefiles located in a large and unwieldy
source code tree. As it turned out, I spent most of the time opening file
requesters, loading one file, then loading another, looking at the files and
starting over. After the 20th file out of about 300 I grew tired of all this
and thought to myself that there must be an easier way to this. Browser is my
solution to this problem.

@{b}Credits@{ub}
Credit where credit is due, Browser is modeled after the file browser window
in the BBEdit text editor distributed by Bare Bones Software, Inc. While the
two share similarities, Browser is an entirely original program which was
written from scratch in about two weeks, starting with 20 March 1998.

@{b}Source code@{ub}
The Browser source code is not placed in the public domain, and it is not
included in the regular program distribution. The source code is copyrighted
and available from the author for a small fee to cover the costs of mailing.
If you are interested in obtaining the source code, send US$ 5.00 and a blank
3˝" disk to the following address:

   Olaf Barthel
   Brabeckstrasse 35
   D-30559 Hannover
   Federal Republic of Germany

If there is enough demand for it, the source code will eventually be made a
permanent part of the regular distribution.

@{b}Distribution@{ub}
Browser is distributed using a concept known as Gift-Ware. If you like the
program and use it frequently, the author wants you to send him a gift of any
kind that could serve as a payment for Browser. Cool Jazz and Be Bop CDs are
among the all time favourites of the author, but feel free to be creative and
send something different. @{i}Thank you!@{ui} Send your contributions to:

   Olaf Barthel
   Brabeckstrasse 35
   D-30559 Hannover
   Federal Republic of Germany

@{b}Commercial use@{ub}
If you are publishing this program on a magazine cover disk, on a software
compilation CD, etc. I would like to have a copy of that magazine or CD
@{b}without having to ask for it@{ub}. If, and only if, I receive that copy you will
get my permission to publish Browser in this form.

@{b}Author@{ub}
If you wish to contact the author of Browser, you can use the following postal
address:

   Olaf Barthel
   Brabeckstrasse 35
   D-30559 Hannover
   Federal Republic of Germany

or you can use this e-mail address:

   olsen@sourcery.han.de
@endnode

@remark ----------------------------------------------------------------------

@node FIND.TEXT.MAIN "Find text"
Once Browser has loaded a text file to display, you can start searching for a
substring in the text body. The following controls are available:

@{" Find             " link FIND.TEXT.PATTERN}
@{" Ignore case      " link FIND.TEXT.IGNORECASE}
@{" Only whole words " link FIND.TEXT.ONLYWORDS}
@{" Scan backwards   " link FIND.TEXT.SCANBACKWARDS}
@{" Find next        " link FIND.TEXT.FINDNEXT}
@{" Cancel           " link FIND.TEXT.CANCEL}
@endnode

@node FIND.TEXT.PATTERN "Text to find"
This is where you enter the text to find in the file displayed in the bottom
half of the Browser window.

Hit @{b}[Return]@{ub} to close the text search window and to begin searching for the
next occurence of the search string.

Hit @{b}[Cursor up]@{ub} to recall the previous search text entered. Hit @{b}[Alt]-[Cursor up]@{ub}
to recall the first search text entered.

Hit @{b}[Cursor down]@{ub} to move around in the search history list. @{b}[Alt]-[Cursor down]@{ub}
will take you to the end of the list.
@endnode

@node FIND.TEXT.USEWILDCARDS "Use wildcards"
This option selects whether Browser should interpret AmigaDOS wildcard
patterns in the search text you specified. If disabled, Browser will check
whether the text found exactly matches the search string.

Not available in the text search window.
@endnode

@node FIND.TEXT.IGNORECASE "Ignore case"
This option selects whether Browser should consider that a text substring
matches the search text if only the case of the characters is different.
This means, a word like @{b}MORE@{ub} is treated the same as @{b}more@{ub}.
@endnode

@node FIND.TEXT.ONLYWORDS "Only whole words"
This option selects whether a text found to match the search string is
accepted only if it occurs as single word and not just as part of a word. This
means, searching for the word @{b}man@{ub} will stop when the text @{b}man@{ub} is found, but
not on the text @{b}caiman@{ub}.
@endnode

@node FIND.TEXT.SCANBACKWARDS "Scan backwards"
This option reverses the direction of the search. Normally, searching starts
at the top of the display, continuing downwards to the end of the file. With
this option enabled, it will still start at the top of the display, but
continue upwards towards the top of the file.
@endnode

@node FIND.TEXT.FINDNEXT "Find next"
Hit this button to start the text search without closing the text search
window.
@endnode

@node FIND.TEXT.CANCEL "Cancel"
Hit this button to close the text search without starting the search process.
@endnode

@remark ----------------------------------------------------------------------

@node FIND.FILE.MAIN "Find file"
Once Browser has read the contents list of a directory, you can start
searching for a file or drawer that may be located in this directory or far
below in one of its subdirectories. Browser will scan the entire filing system
hierarchy below this directory and even follow links and multiple volume
assignments. The following controls are available:

@{" Find             " link FIND.FILE.PATTERN}
@{" Use wildcards    " link FIND.FILE.USEWILDCARDS}
@{" Start search     " link FIND.FILE.STARTSEARCH}
@{" Cancel           " link FIND.FILE.CANCEL}
@endnode

@node FIND.FILE.PATTERN "File name pattern to find"
This is where you enter the name of the file or drawer to find in the
directory and all its subdirectories.

Hit @{b}[Return]@{ub} to close the file search window and to start searching for
matching file and drawer names.

Hit @{b}[Cursor up]@{ub} to recall the previous search text entered. Hit @{b}[Alt]-[Cursor up]@{ub}
to recall the first search text entered.

Hit @{b}[Cursor down]@{ub} to move around in the search history list. @{b}[Alt]-[Cursor down]@{ub}
will take you to the end of the list.
@endnode

@node FIND.FILE.USEWILDCARDS "Use wildcards"
This option selects whether Browser should interpret AmigaDOS wildcard
patterns in the search text you specified. If disabled, Browser will check
whether the text found exactly matches the search string.
@endnode

@node FIND.FILE.IGNORECASE "Ignore case"
This option selects whether Browser should consider that a text substring
matches the search text if only the case of the characters is different.

Not available in the file search window since comparisons are by default
case-insensitive.
@endnode

@node FIND.FILE.ONLYWORDS "Only whole words"
This option selects whether a text found to match the search string is
accepted only if it occurs as single word and not just as part of a word. This
means, searching for the word @{b}man@{ub} will stop when the text @{b}man@{ub} is found, but
not on the text @{b}caiman@{ub}.

Not available in the file search window.
@endnode

@node FIND.FILE.SCANBACKWARDS "Scan backwards"
This option reverses the direction of the search. Normally, searching starts
at the top of the display, continuing downwards to the end of the file. With
this option enabled, it will still start at the top of the display, but
continue upwards towards the top of the file.

Not available in the file search window.
@endnode

@node FIND.FILE.STARTSEARCH "Start search"
Hit this button to start the file search without closing the file search
window.
@endnode

@node FIND.FILE.CANCEL "Cancel"
Hit this button to close the text search without starting the search process.
Note that closing the window will not stop a search process already in
progress.
@endnode

@remark ----------------------------------------------------------------------

@node GADGET.DRAWER "Drawer name"
This is the name of the volume or directory whose contents are displayed in the
list below.
@endnode

@node GADGET.DIRLIST "Directory list"
This list shows the names of volumes, drawers and files that can be entered or
displayed. To move around in the list and to use its contents, see the
following topics:

@{" List of keyboard shortcuts " link KEYBOARD}
@{" List of mouse commands     " link MOUSE}
@endnode

@node GADGET.TEXTLIST "Text display"
This list shows the contents of a file.
@endnode

@node GADGET.SEPARATOR "Separator"
The directory list and the text display are separated by this small bar. To
change the sizes of the directory list and the text display, click on this bar
with the left mouse button, drag the bar to its new location and release the
left mouse button.
@endnode

@node GADGET.MESSAGEDISPLAY "Message display"
This display shows error messages and information about the text file being
displayed in the list above it.
@endnode

@node GADGET.DIRSTATUSDISPLAY "Directory status display"
This display shows error messages and information about the directory list
displayed above it.
@endnode

@remark ----------------------------------------------------------------------

@node MENU.MAIN "Menu items"
The Browser commands are grouped into six pull-down menus:

@{b}Project@{ub}

  @{" New                         " link MENU.NEW }
  @{" Duplicate                   " link MENU.DUPLICATE }
  @{" Close                       " link MENU.CLOSE }
  @{" Activate next browser       " link MENU.NEXT }
  @{" Activate previous browser   " link MENU.PREVIOUS }
  @{" Free caches                 " link MENU.FREECACHES }
  @{" About...                    " link MENU.ABOUT }
  @{" Quit                        " link MENU.QUIT }

@{b}Edit@{ub}

  @{" Copy file name to clipboard " link MENU.COPYNAME }
  @{" Open with editor...         " link MENU.EDIT }

@{b}Directory@{ub}

  @{" Parent                      " link MENU.PARENT }
  @{" Volumes                     " link MENU.VOLUMES }
  @{" Open                        " link MENU.OPEN }
  @{" Open in next browser        " link MENU.OPENNEXT }
  @{" Change drawer...            " link MENU.CHANGEDRAWER }
  @{" Reread drawer               " link MENU.REREADDRAWER }
  @{" Stop reading                " link MENU.STOPREADING }
  @{" Sort by name                " link MENU.SORTALPHA }
  @{" Sort by size                " link MENU.SORTSIZE }
  @{" Sort by date                " link MENU.SORTDATE }
  @{" Natural order               " link MENU.NATURAL }
  @{" Reverse order               " link MENU.REVERSE }

@{b}Find@{ub}

  @{" Find file...                " link MENU.FINDFILE }
  @{" Find text...                " link MENU.FINDTEXT }
  @{" Find text again             " link MENU.FINDTEXTAGAIN }

@{b}Organize windows@{ub}

  @{" Stack windows               " link MENU.STACKWINDOWS }
  @{" Tile windows                " link MENU.TILEWINDOWS }
  @{" Cascade windows             " link MENU.CASCADEWINDOWS }

@{b}Help@{ub}

  General...
  Keyboard shortcuts...
@endnode

@remark ----------------------------------------------------------------------

@node MENU.NEW "New"
Select this menu item to open a new empty Browser window.
@endnode

@node MENU.DUPLICATE "Duplicate"
Select this menu item to open a new Browser window with the same directory
list and text display contents as the currently active Browser window.
@endnode

@node MENU.CLOSE "Close"
This menu item will close the active Browser window. If this is the last
Browser window, the program will exit.
@endnode

@node MENU.NEXT "Activate next browser"
This will activate the next following Browser window and make it visible.
@endnode

@node MENU.PREVIOUS "Activate previous browser"
This will activate the preceding Browser window and make it visible.
@endnode

@node MENU.ABOUT "About"
This menu item displays the copyright and usage information.
@endnode

@node MENU.QUIT "Quit"
This terminates the program and all other Browser applications.
@endnode

@remark ----------------------------------------------------------------------

@node MENU.COPYNAME "Copy file name to clipboard"
This will copy the complete name of the drawer or file currently selected in
the directory list to the clipboard.
@endnode

@node MENU.EDIT "Open with editor"
If there is a text file loaded, this will launch the text editor on the file.

Note that this requires the @{b}EDITOR@{ub} environment variable to be set up properly.
@endnode

@remark ----------------------------------------------------------------------

@node MENU.PARENT "Parent"
This menu item moves up to the parent of the currently displayed directory. If
you are already at the top directory of a volume, the volume and assignment
list will be displayed.
@endnode

@node MENU.VOLUMES "Volumes"
This menu item will display the list of volumes and assignments.
@endnode

@node MENU.OPEN "Open"
This menu item opens the currently selected file or drawer.

When reading a file, Browser examines the first 128 bytes to see whether the
file in question is a plain text or binary file. If there are less than 75%
plain text characters in these first 128 bytes, then the file contents will be
displayed in hexadecimal format
@endnode

@node MENU.OPENNEXT "Open in next browser"
This menu item opens the currently selected file or drawer in the next
following Browser; if there is no such Browser window yet, it will be opened.
@endnode

@node MENU.CHANGEDRAWER "Change drawer"
This menu item will activate the @{"drawer name" link GADGET.DRAWER} text entry field for you to make
changes to the drawer name.
@endnode

@node MENU.REREADDRAWER "Reread drawer"
This menu item will cause the directory list to be reread and updated.
@endnode

@node MENU.SORTALPHA "Sort by name"
This menu item will cause the directory list to be sorted by name.
@endnode

@node MENU.SORTSIZE "Sort by size"
This menu item will cause the directory list to be sorted by the sizes of the
files.
@endnode

@node MENU.SORTDATE "Sort by date"
This menu item will cause the directory list to be sorted by the modification
dates of the drawers and files.
@endnode

@node MENU.NATURAL "Natural order"
This menu item will cause the directory list to be sorted in ascending order.
@endnode

@node MENU.REVERSE "Reverse order"
This menu item will cause the directory list to be sorted in descending order.
@endnode

@remark ----------------------------------------------------------------------

@node MENU.FINDFILE "Find file"
This menu item opens the @{"file find window" link FIND.FILE.MAIN}.
@endnode

@node MENU.FINDTEXT "Find text"
This menu item opens the @{"text find window" link FIND.TEXT.MAIN}.
@endnode

@node MENU.FINDTEXTAGAIN "Find text again"
This menu item repeats the previous text find operation. If there was no
previous text find operation, the @{"text find window" link FIND.TEXT.MAIN}. will be opened.
@endnode

@remark ----------------------------------------------------------------------

@node MENU.STACKWINDOWS "Stack windows"
This menu item causes all Browser windows on the same screen as the active
window to be placed below one another.
@endnode

@node MENU.TILEWINDOWS "Tile windows"
This menu item causes all Browser windows on the same screen as the active
window to be placed right next to one another.
@endnode

@node MENU.CASCADEWINDOWS "Cascade windows"
This menu item causes all Browser windows on the same screen as the active
window to overlap one another.
@endnode

@node MENU.FREECACHES "Free caches"
When browsing through a directory tree, Browser retains copies of every
directory list it displays. Unless the directory contents change while you are
watching a different directory list, this allows Browser to display
directories quickly, once they have been visited. Naturally, this buffering
takes up memory which can accumulate over time. Use the menu item "Free
caches" to release all the memory allocated for directories that are not
currently being displayed.
@endnode

@node MENU.STOPREADING "Stop reading"
At times you may want to stop Browser reading from the file you have just
selected in the directory list. In such a case, use this menu item.
@endnode
